race.comment: Tricky way to start things on Penshurst Cup Day and siding with FRENCH LOVE (6), who is a 13-start maiden but has run her two best races at her past two starts, when beaten in a photo in both. Only needs to run up to those efforts to be the testing material. NEVRA QUEEN (8) did little at her first start but was put away after that and the first-up run over 1400m was a suitable warm-up for a race like this. Drawn out a little, but likely to go back anyway and with added fitness she can figure. SO REGAL (9), on the other hand, is at peak fitness now and while never a factor last start, it was a much tougher race than this - the winner ran in the VRC Oaks - and she only needs to get back to the form of the previous two starts to be a key player. AUSTRAL MISS (5) is another with upside who's better for three runs, the latest at around this trip. IMACREEDYTWO (3) jumped from 1000m to 1300m last start and ran an improved race so will be ready to fire third-up at this trip.
